data.database_description: This database appears to manage information related to parties (which could be individuals or organizations), their services, forms they complete, addresses, and contact details. It tracks relationships between parties, such as which individuals are associated with which organizations, and records when specific forms are completed. The schema also captures details about the types of services provided and the forms used in these services, including descriptions and identifiers for each.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for an address.
First line of the address, typically including street number and building name.
Town or city part of the address.
Postal code or ZIP code for the address.
State, province, or county part of the address.
Country part of the address.

sample_data: 1, 25518 Ortiz Centers, West Stacy, 193, NorthCarolina, USA
2, 033 Stracke Parkways, Lake Meaghan, 227, Colorado, USA
3, 269 Flatley Port Suite 062, Breanneberg, 527, NewHampshire, USA

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each service.
Code indicating the type of the service (e.g., Education, Welfare).
Name of the service.
Detailed description of the service.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Contains details about different services provided, including their types, names, and descriptions.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each form.
Code indicating the type of the form (e.g., Basic, Complex).
Identifier linking the form to a specific service.
Unique number assigned to each form.
Name of the form.
Detailed description of the form's purpose and content.

sample_data: 1, Basic, 13, 8069, SSN Application, Form for SSN Application
enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores information about various forms used in services, including their types, associated service IDs, numbers, names, and descriptions.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each individual.
First name of the individual.
Middle name of the individual.
Phone number of the individual.
Email address of the individual.
Address of the individual.
Last name of the individual.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores information about individuals, including their names, contact details, and address.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each organization.
Date when the organization was formed.
Name of the organization.
VAT number of the organization (specific to the UK).

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores information about organizations, including their formation date, name, and VAT number.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each party.
Code representing the payment method used by the party.
Phone number associated with the party.
Email address associated with the party.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores information about parties, including individuals and organizations.

columns.columnDescription: Identifier for the individual, linking to the Individuals table.
Identifier for the organization, linking to the Organizations table.
Start date of the contact relationship between the individual and the organization.
End date of the contact relationship between the individual and the organization.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Links individuals to organizations and records the period during which the contact relationship was active.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for a party.
Unique identifier for an address, linked to the Addresses table.
Start date of the address association with the party.
Type of address (e.g., Residence, Billing, Delivery).
End date of the address association with the party.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Associates parties with their addresses and specifies the type and duration of the association.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for the party associated with the form.
Unique identifier for the form completed by the party.
Date and time when the form completion process started.
Code indicating the current status of the form (e.g., Completed, Partially Completed, Not Started).
Date and time when the form was fully completed.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Records information about forms completed by parties, including the status and completion dates.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each booking.
Identifier for the party (individual or organization) making the booking.
Identifier for the service being booked.
Date and time when the service is scheduled to be performed.
Date when the booking was made.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Records bookings for services provided to parties.
